  <section class="usa-graphic-list usa-section usa-section--dark">
    <div class="grid-container">
      <div class="usa-graphic-list__row grid-row grid-gap">
        <div class="usa-media-block tablet:grid-col">
          <a href=""><img class="usa-media-block__img" src="/{{ active_theme_path() }}/images/circle-uvindex.png"
              alt="Alt text"></a>
          <div class="usa-media-block__body">
            <h3 class="usa-graphic-list__heading"><a href="" style="color:#00bde3;">UV Index Forecasts</a></h3>
            <p>The ultraviolet index or UV Index is an international standard measurement of the strength of sunburn-producing ultraviolet (UV) radiation at a particular place and time.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="usa-media-block tablet:grid-col">
          <a href=""><img class="usa-media-block__img" src="/{{ active_theme_path() }}/images/circle-enso.png"
              alt="Alt text"></a>
          <div class="usa-media-block__body">
            <h3 class="usa-graphic-list__heading"><a href="" style="color:#00bde3;">El Niño & La Niña</a></h3>
            <p>El Niño & La Niña refer to both the warm and cool phases of the El Niño Southern Oscillation (ENSO), a large-scale ocean-atmosphere climate phenomenon.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="usa-graphic-list__row grid-row grid-gap">
        <div class="usa-media-block tablet:grid-col">
          <a href=""><img class="usa-media-block__img" src="/{{ active_theme_path() }}/images/circle-drought.png"
              alt="Alt text"></a>
          <div class="usa-media-block__body">
            <h3 class="usa-graphic-list__heading"><a href="" style="color:#00bde3;">U.S. Drought Information</a></h3>
            <p>Drought is a deficiency in precipitation over an extended period. The U.S. Drought Monitor (USDM) is a weekly product that provides a general summary of current drought conditions.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="usa-media-block tablet:grid-col">
          <a href=""><img class="usa-media-block__img" src="/{{ active_theme_path() }}/images/circle-ddhi.png"
              alt="Alt text"></a>
          <div class="usa-media-block__body">
            <h3 class="usa-graphic-list__heading"><a href="" style="color:#00bde3;">Degree Days &amp; Heat Index</a></h3>
            <p>Degree days are measures of how cold or warm a location is. The heat index is what the temperature feels like to the human body when relative humidity is combined with the air temperature.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

